You are working on the Attrove quickstart — the full B2B2B provisioning flow.

Tech stack: TypeScript, Node.js 18+, ES modules, @attrove/sdk, vitest.

SDK rules:
- Always use @attrove/sdk — never raw fetch
- Server-side: Attrove.admin({ clientId, clientSecret }) for provisioning
- Client-side: new Attrove({ apiKey, userId }) for queries
- brief(), entity(), thread() DO NOT EXIST — they will cause compile errors
- The SDK defaults to https://api.attrove.com — no baseUrl needed

Authentication flow:
1. Partner uses client_id + client_secret to create users
2. admin.users.create() returns sk_ API key per user
3. admin.users.createConnectToken() returns pit_ token (10 min, single-use)
4. User visits connect URL to authorize Gmail/Slack/etc via OAuth
5. Partner queries user data with sk_ token

This example has a --demo flag that shows mock output without credentials.
Environment: ATTROVE_CLIENT_ID + ATTROVE_CLIENT_SECRET (partner credentials, not user tokens).
